verbs.description: unbox (third-person singular simple present unboxes, present participle unboxing, simple past and past participle unboxed)

entries.meaning: (transitive, computing) To retrieve (a value of a primitive type) from the object in which it is boxed.
examples: When a boxing or unboxing operation occurs in code, whether it was implicit or explicit, the IL generated includes the box or unbox command.
